-##
-# Bootstrap Heading
-# All HTML headings, h1 through h6, are available. .h1 through .h6 classes
-# are also available, for when you want to match the font styling of a heading
-# but still want your text to be displayed inline.
-#
-# Locals
-# :small - String - Optional - Small description
-# :text  - String - Required - Main text
-# :type  - String - Required - Heading Tag H1 - H6 - Default H6
-#
-# Usage
-# -# Heading
-# = partial "bootstrap/type/heading",
-#            :locals => { :small => "Secondary text",
-#                         :text  => "Heading",
-#                         :type  => "h1" }
-#
-# @author Ian Warner <ian.warner@drykiss.com>
-# @see    http://getbootstrap.com/css/#type-headings
-# @todo
-##

-# Type Default
- if ! locals[ :type ]
    - type = "h1"

-# Heading
- haml_tag type do

    -# Main Text
    = text

    -# Add the secondary text if required
    - if locals[ :small ]
        %small= small